Durban - One person was killed and 16 injured in a collision between a minibus taxi and a light delivery vehicle on Chris Hani (North Coast) Road in Durban on Monday night.  Emer-G-Med paramedics and other emergency services responded to the scene. Kyle van Reenen, spokesperson for Emer-G-Med paramedics, said that paramedics responded to the scene of a collision involving a minibus taxi and a light delivery vehicle at the intersection of Chris Hani Road and Victor Roads in the Avoca area.  “On arrival on scene a triage area was established by scene commanders and it was established that as many as 16 people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious.” Van Reenen added that the driver of a Ford Bantam bakkie had suffered fatal injuries and was declared dead on arrival of paramedics.  “The injured were treated and stabilised on scene before being taken to various nearby hospitals by ambulances for further treatment.” Earlier on Monday, Emer-G-Med paramedics attended a crash scene where a motorcyclist was struck by a heavy-duty vehicle on the N2 south near the uMngeni River. Van Reenen said that the 30-year-old male motorcyclist had been lucky to escape with only minor injuries.  “Emer-G-Med paramedics together with KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Emergency Services arrived on scene to find the man lying in the centre median.” Van Reenen said that the motorcyclist received the necessary medical attention.  “He was treated and stabilised on scene before being taken to a nearby hospital for further care.” THE MERCURY